after HIV infection, the specific oxidative and nitrosative species that are 
involved in the post-translational modification of the brain proteome, and the 
methods that are currently used for the detection of such modified proteins. 
This review also provides an overview of related research pertaining to 
oxidative stress-related HAND using cerebrospinal fluid and human brain tissue.

