Do cervical collars and cervicothoracic orthoses effectively stabilize the 
injured cervical spine? A biomechanical investigation.

Ivancic PC(1).

Author information:
(1)Biomechanics Research Laboratory, Department of Orthopaedics and 
Rehabilitation, Yale University School of Medicine, New Haven, CT 06520, USA. 
paul.ivancic@yale.edu

STUDY DESIGN: In vitro biomechanical study.
OBJECTIVE: Our objective was to determine the effectiveness of cervical collars 
and cervicothoracic orthoses for stabilizing clinically relevant, experimentally 
produced cervical spine injuries.
